James de Villiers, News24 (Picture: Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Vanderbijlpark &ndash; An 18-month-old child drowned in a swimming pool in a residential complex in Vanderbijlpark on Tuesday afternoon, paramedics said.When paramedics arrived on scene they found the grandmother performing CPR on the child, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said.&nbsp;Paramedics initiated advanced life support interventions.&nbsp;After an hour, the child still showed no signs of life and was declared dead.&nbsp;Additional information surrounding the incident was not immediately known.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.